data.enText: the act of suddenly leaving a meeting as a protest against sth
data.chText: （为表示抗议而突然的）退场，退席

means: (为表示抗议而突然的)退场，退席

tr: the act of walking out (of a meeting or organization) as a sign of protest
example: there was a walkout by the Black members as the chairman rose to speak

tr: a strike in which the workers walk out

example.ex: The commission's proceedings have been wrecked by tantrums and walkouts.
example.tran: 委员会的议程因与会者的撒泼捣乱和离席抗议而受阻。

value.def: If there is a walkout during a meeting, some or all of the people attending it leave in order to show their disapproval of something that has happened at the meeting.
value.tran: (会议上表示反对的)离席，退场
